{
  "text": "A traditional way of adding more representational power to a neural network is layer stacking. RNN stacking has been successfully used in a lot of [CITATION_1] . However, stacking layers of neural networks suffers from the degradation problem [CITATION_2] . This is due to the difficulty in training a lot of stacked layers and fit these layers to desired underlying mappings, which leads to representational degradation.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "11590585",
